-- Greek credit shrinks 4.1 pct y/y in March
-- 
-- Wed May 21, 2014 05:20AM EDT
-- None



ATHENS, May 21 (Reuters) - Total credit in Greece shrank 4.1 percent year-on-year in March, with the pace of decline slowing from the previous month, Bank of Greece <BOGr.AT> data showed on Wednesday.

Credit extended to the government fell 4.3 percent after shrinking by 9.3 percent in February, the central bank said. Lending to businesses and households also declined, by 4.1 percent compared to a 4.0 percent decline in February. ************************************************************* KEY FIGURES (in pct y/y)MARCH  FEB  JAN   DEC   NOV   OCT Total credit-4.1  -4.7 -5.5  -6.0  -7.6  -7.9 Credit to public sector -4.4  -9.3-13.9 -18.1 -27.1 -28.6 Credit to business, hholds  -4.1  -4.0 -4.0  -3.9  -3.8  -3.9 -------------------------------------------------------------